         Outlook (magazine)   From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia   Jump to: navigation , search    Outlook    The 17th Anninersary Issue of Outlook     Editor in Chief  Rajesh Ramachandran    Categories  News magazine    Circulation  425,000 [1]    Publisher  Outlook Publishing India Pvt. Ltd.    First issue  October 1995 ; 22 years ago ( 1995-10 )    Country  India    Based in  New Delhi    Language  English    Website  www.outlookindia.com    Outlook is a weekly general interest English  news magazine published in India . [2] [3]     Contents    1  History and profile  2  Staff   2.1  Editors in Chief  2.2  Editors  2.3  Managing Editors  2.4  Notable Contributors    3  References  4  External links     History and profile [ edit ]  Outlook was first issued in October 1995 with Vinod Mehta as the editor in chief . [4] The magazine is owned by the Raheja group. [5] The publisher is Outlook Publishing India Pvt. Ltd. [6] It features contents from politics, sports, cinema, and stories of broad interests.  Staff [ edit ]  Editors in Chief [ edit ]   Rajesh Ramachandran (2016)  Ruben Banerjee   Editors [ edit ]   Vinod Mehta (1995 - 2012) Editor [7]  Krishna Prasad (2012–2016)  Rajesh Ramachandran (2016)   Managing Editors [ edit ]   Tarun Tejpal (1995 - March, 2000) [8]   Notable Contributors [ edit ]   Vinod Mehta  Arundhati Roy   References [ edit ]     ^  IRS 2014 Topline Findings  mruc.net . Retrieved 31 March 2013. Archived 7 April 2014 at Wayback Machine .  ^  India: Newspapers and Magazines Online  worldpress.org . Retrieved 31 March 2013  ^  Politicians, journalists should never be friends:Vinod Mehta  livemint.com . Retrieved 31 March 2013  ^  "Vinod Mehta, editor of India's Outlook magazine, dies at 73" . Arab News . AP. 8 March 2015 . Retrieved 20 November 2016 .   ^  "2. Which business family owns the Outlook Publishing group?" . Retrieved 6 January 2015 .   ^  "Outlook group to relaunch Newsweek in India by Apr" . Business Standard . New Delhi. 24 Febr